hey so i’m trying to recall the extent of our conversation around library type Dxs on friday. 

did we conclude that it’s now supposed to be “heart”ing a session and a corresponding list of favorites instead of checkboxes and a session history list?? 

furthermore, was our discussion around the checkbox an issue of placement or icon appearance? trying to figure out if this heart needs a different home than to the side of the card in current designs
Right now I think a star has been used to indicate saving tips.

my understanding was that yes we need to change it to a heart, that it was the fact that it was an empty checkbox that was throwing christian off. that will save the session in a list of your favorites, which is what “History” is changing to
Elise is working on updating the wireframes accordingly, so you can always hit her up with additional clarifying questions
thanks Ali and Abby
<@U026PLK4S> do you recall specifics on placement of this heart? did we want to find a place for it on the actual card itself and move away from the icon being to the side of the card?
i think that’s what we want to keep exploring. i don’t think we came up with a prescriptive answer. But I may be wrong.

I wanted to double check with the group about the dx cards states (color, grey tone or white wash) in particular completed dx cards. I’m just wondering whether to use grey cards or white washed cards for the completed Dx in the Dx Library History.
i think we wanted to move away from the white wash, i remember scott saying he likes the grey treatment and likes the “grittiness"
<@U026PLK4S>: is that what you got?
yep
awesome, thanks!
just to clarify, we had been using grey and white washes for slightly separate meanings. are we now using the grey all across the board (two color states instead of three)?
actually, we still want to keep the three. light grey just replaces the white wash
i’m trying to set up a new CPU which is taking some time. happy to chat once i’m finished
that would be great, not sure i know what the light grey wash is supposed to look like

<!channel> Hey visual design team! Couple of things - 1. You’ll see that we pushed the tomorrow design meeting with adidas to Thursday at 3pm. This is so we have a bit more time and can show a more complete picture then. So let’s push to make any changes/tweaks from Friday feedback *today*, and get out flats by EOD. Then let’s push forward to get Home detail / Add activity screens designed and internally reviewed by 3pm.

There’s also one more new section, which is onboarding. Matt’s going to think through who we need and can put on that task this week. Let’s push to show designs for onboarding as well, dependent on how far we get and what state they are in.

Lastly, there are a lot of moving parts as we’re moving into  a real production mode this and next week. Jenna and I have a good grasp on what needs to be done, so if you are confused or out of work at any point, please let us know. :slightly_smiling_face: Thanks!
